# Superseded calibration profiles — kept on disk, not repo source. Only the
# current *operating* profile is tracked (§10 firmware<->ML contract); it is
# cal_63_air_v2.json, which is deliberately absent from this list.
#
# Listed file-by-file rather than as `src/data/profiles/*` + a negation: the
# wildcard form is correct as far as git is concerned, but the dir/* + !negation
# idiom renders unreliably in some editors' ignore decorations. The trade-off is
# that new delaycal candidate profiles are NOT ignored by default — add each
# superseded lock here as it is retired.
src/data/profiles/cal_63_air_v1.json
src/data/profiles/cal_72_air_v2.json
src/data/profiles/cal_72_air_v3.json

